core:process.core:name: GetCardNumber
core:process.core:comment: Capture a customer's card number by Swiping, Keying or Scanning, or, optionally, using the ICC reader. Not for use in card tendering. If ICC reader is used, user is prompted to remove the card once read. If AllowSkip is set the process will exit on pressing OK with no input (default false). If AllowCancel is set the cancel button will be available (default true).

core:assignAction.core:comment: Increment retry count, goto fallback if retries == max attempts

core:executeProcessAction.core:comment: Remove card now - we only wanted the card number.

core:state.core:comment: This state is needed so that the GetCardNumber prompt state is no longer listening on events. Otherwise any events that come in while we are in the DoICCApplicationSelection process will be acted upon from GetCardNumber, and also possibly in the called process if they are listened to there as well.

core:messageState.core:comment: The IC card could not be read
